  "message": "<h2>Changelog for DiGidot C4 Firmware v2.0.3 - Released on 5-7-2019</h2>\n\n<h5>Added</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Interface: Show connection status</li>\n<li>Interface: Add extra error message pop-up</li>\n<li>Interface: Add IC picker</li>\n<li>Interface: Show beta firmware at update page</li>\n<li>Interface: Change title of playlist</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Changed</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>IO: By default, the gamma correction is now disabled</li>\n<li>Interface: Auto select first universe of device at Art-Net watcher</li>\n<li>Interface: Make timeout for long press on playbar sliders longer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Improved</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Output: It's now possible to drive up to 8 universes (4096 channels) on 1 port of the C4. Please keep in mind that we always suggest a maximum of 3 universes on 1 port or 6 universes if you have a data/clock IC</li>\n<li>Interface: More validation on inputs/form in general</li>\n<li>Interface: Styling for mobile phones</li>\n<li>Interface: Port limit page styling</li>\n<li>Interface: Backup items list styling</li>\n<li>Interface: Colorpicker hsv saturation and brightness </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Fixed</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>microSD: Fixed an issue where a field in the scene header will be duplicated multiple times when upgrading  scenes from 1.x to 2.x</li>\n<li>WiFi: When using C4 in Open AP mode, if new settings are applied, the 'state' command gives correct information again</li>\n<li>HTTP-GET: When using HTTP-GET with accounts, the C4 will no longer crash anymore</li>\n<li>Logging: If the C4 encounters a critical error, the LOG on the SD-card is now valid JSON again</li>\n<li>Interface: Create/restore backup with device name and order </li>\n<li>Interface: Fix analog calibration inputs</li>\n<li>Interface: Load scenes with Android 6</li>\n<li>Interface: 'Buy license' link</li>\n<li>Interface: Colorpicker saturation and brightness fix</li>\n<li>Interface: Escape colorpicker bugfix</li>\n<li>Interface: Fixing playlist current playing scene index in playerbar</li>\n<li>Interface: On various moments the interface no longer shifts up so parts become hidden</li>\n</ul>\n"
}